07/03/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and his Slovenian counterpart, Janez Jansa, held an unannounced meeting Sunday (6 March) on ways to resolve open bilateral issues. They agreed on the need for a joint commission on border problems and for a future agreement on avoidance of double taxation. Jansa expressed the hope that Croatia would prove it was fully co-operating with the UN war crimes tribunal and start accession talks with the EU on 17 March as planned. (HRT, HINA - 07/03/05)
